The '''ZyXEL''' logo, "45-401-000728", and "Made in Taiwan" is silkscreened :on the board in the FCC photos. Some (/ all?) production boards are made in China, and note it as such. :The FCC label states the default SSID is '''ZyXEL'''.
===Forum threads=== *[http://www.dd-wrt.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=74854 ''ZyXEL NBG334W EE (AR2317)'' on the '''DD-WRT''' forums] (w/ board shot) :This device is using [[Atheros]] AR2317 (AR2317-AC1A) *[http://www.dd-wrt.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=75023 ''ZyXEL NBG334W DD-WRT support'' (main thread) on the '''DD-WRT''' forums] :Boot log indicates stock usage of '''Bootbase''' bootloader and '''ZyNOS'''
===Reviews=== *[http://www.ixbt.com/comm/zyxel-nbg334w.shtml ''ZyXEL NBG334W'' on '''iXBT'''] (RU)
===Probable used PSU(s)=== Two power supplies are shown in the FCC photos - one for AC models :(may be more common, if not exclusively such) and one for DC models.
